Andrej Karpathy is a prominent figure in the field of artificial intelligence and deep learning. He has a background in computer science and physics, with extensive experience in training deep neural networks on large datasets. Andrej Karpathy has worked at Tesla as the Sr. Director of AI, led the computer vision team of Tesla Autopilot, and was a founding member at OpenAI. Additionally, he has made significant contributions to the development of convolutional and recurrent neural networks, as well as their applications in computer vision and natural language processing.
